    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing - Removal -
        Crankcase Rear Cover and Power Steering Idler Shaft
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s12.2.8" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Crankcase Rear Cover and Power Steering Idler Shaft</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, support engine (if in chassis) before removing rear cover or
                    engine mounts.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3450012021" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM10/M10119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankcase rear cover mounting bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 55 bolt (5)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 70 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 60 bolt (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 11 mounting bolts from crankcase rear cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, when removing crankcase rear cover, do not pull out gasket between upper
                    and lower crankcase.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a thin gasket scraper to separate sealant between rear gear cover gasket and upper and
                lower crankcase joint. This will avoid pulling the gasket out when removing crankcase rear cover
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, get help when removing or installing the crankcase rear
                    cover.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove crankcase rear cover with aid of an assistant.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard rear gear cover gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, use a
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_268.xml" xrefid="s12.t3">slide hammer</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s12.t3"/>
                to remove power steering idler shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
